Find command: find name and tags
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command only checks name for keywords.

A find which can search both names and tags is more user-friendly as
users can search for people through their names or what they are
tagged as.

Let's update the search algorithm to search both names and tags and
rename the predicate handling the search to better reflect what it
now does.

Duplicate detection: Increase number of checks
commitResults.messageBody:
Duplicate detection only detects whether two person have the exact
same name whereby there are many people with the same name.

Duplicate detection which ignores whitespaces and capitalization will
encompase more cases of duplicates detected along with specific fields
which should not be able to be the same for different people.

Let's improve duplicate detection to detect similar names along with at
least one field which is the same to conclude whether someone is a
duplicate contact.

commitResults.messageBody:
A bug was reported that prefix of existing command should show error
message, despite of the warning given in the user guide. Another bug
reported is that alias can contain existing command word.

Alias replacement is done if it matches a word instead of substring.
Additional check is created when parsing addalias command.

It helps to create a more robust system.

Resolves: #151, #142
